body:
there is no one click option but i found this trick really useful :
- install Jist   

  gem install jist

  (you need to sync Jist with your git account in order to post gist on githum)
- add this in 

  .ipython/your_profile/static/js/custom.js

##

``` javacript
$([IPython.events]).on('notebook_loaded.Notebook', function(){
    IPython.toolbar.add_buttons_group([
                    {
                'label'   : 'Share Notebook nbviewer',
                'icon'    : 'ui-icon-info', 
                'callback': function(){
                                       IPython.notebook.insert_cell_at_bottom('code');
                                       var code = 'lines = !jist -p ' + IPython.notebook.notebook_name + '.ipynb' +
                                                  '\nprint lines[0].replace("https://gist.github.com", "http://nbviewer.ipython.org")';
                                       IPython.notebook.get_cell(-1).set_text(code);
                                       IPython.notebook.save_notebook();
                                       IPython.notebook.get_cell(-1).execute();
                                       }
                    }]);
});
```

this should add a button on the toolbar, it's execution will add and execute a cell at the end of the notebook with 2 lines :

``` python
lines = !jist -p notebook_name.ipynb
print lines[0].replace("https://gist.github.com", "http://nbviewer.ipython.org")
```

it will give you a link to nbviewer

(doesn't work if the notebook name has space in it .. and you need to cd into the directory where the notebook is)

